## üìù Key Points

### Must Have
- Consistent modular type scale (1.2 or 1.25 ratio)
- Systematic spacing (4px or 8px base unit)
- Clear color hierarchy (3-4 levels maximum)
- Single primary focal point per page
- Proper grouping of related elements

### Do
- Use size to indicate importance
- Create clear levels of visual prominence
- Group related items with proximity
- Maintain generous whitespace
- Follow natural reading patterns (F/Z)
- Combine multiple hierarchy techniques
- Test with actual content
- Limit focal points (1 primary per section)

### Don't
- Don't use random font sizes
- Don't apply equal emphasis everywhere
- Don't separate related elements
- Don't create competing focal points
- Don't rely on color alone for hierarchy
- Don't ignore reading patterns
- Don't overcrowd interfaces
- Don't bold/uppercase everything

